cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language modeling. The paper also proposes a new model that marginalizes over all possible composition trees, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses a recently proposed sentence level evaluation metric, which could make it relevant to the sub-category cs.SD (Sound).
